I'm not sure where you got this idea. V8 does not optimize tail calls. It's easy to see this in the Chrome console, I just entered this now:<p><pre><code>  var a = function(x) { if (x == 0) return 'done'; return a(x-1); };
  a(100000);
  RangeError: Maximum call stack size exceeded
</code></pre>
<a href="http://code.google.com/p/v8/issues/detail?id=457" rel="nofollow">http://code.google.com/p/v8/issues/detail?id=457</a>
